No hate to Mr. OP, but it's funny how Millennials tend to speak in this sense of vague potentialities, like events either happen or not only by fate, when "marrying ur gf" is an action you perform by will. It's like saying "if I don't brush my teeth". Stripping of responsibility.

It's what Dr. Ray Peat pointed out about the culture, people suffer learned helplessness en masse because of a lack of "meaningful" choice and "meaningful" activities in life. If nothing you do matters and you cruise down the rail, eventually you forget you can do stuff yourself.
